quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  96,19,"Nay! (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)! Do not obey him (Abû Jahl). Fall prostrate and draw near to Allâh!"
  100,7,"And to that he bears witness (by his deeds)."
  100,8,"And verily, he is violent in the love of wealth."
  100,9,"Knows he not that when the contents of the graves are poured forth (all mankind is resurrected)?"
  101,4,"It is a Day whereon mankind will be like moths scattered about."
  101,5,"And the mountains will be like carded wool."
  101,6,"Then as for him whose balance (of good deeds) will be heavy,{1}",footnotes:1:[{101:6} See footnote of {7:8}.]
  102,1,"The mutual rivalry (for piling up of worldly things) diverts you,"
  102,2,"Until you visit the graves (i.e. till you die)."
  102,3,"Nay! You shall come to know!"